{
  "stem": "868.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But at that, that time, that was the only thing that remains in my memory now.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "What happened next-- as soon as my uncle was assassinated, we figured it's time, time to go.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we escaped illegally across the border into France in September, 1933.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That's my parents, my brother, and I.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we came to-- we came to Paris, where an organization was already established.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I'm not sure, but I believe it was the Joint, which was commonly referred to as the Joint, but that's a short word for a much longer title.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] We were given temporary permits of residence, which had to be extended every three or six, six months.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] My father, again, without work permit, travelled the suburbs of Paris selling textiles.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "You didn't have a, a ready-to-wear industry at the time.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So people would select the fabric and then go to their tailor to have suits made, or whatever, jackets, pants.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So that's what he was selling.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And every few months, we would have to go to the prefecture, as it was called, to have the visa extended.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And this was at a time when France was flooded with refugees, mainly from Spain, because of the Civil War there.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] I have experienced nothing but dislike of foreigners from the French authorities at the time.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I already spoke French well, but my father didn't.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So I went with him every time the visa had to be extended.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And it was always a, a, a most unpleasant experience.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "They made you wait most of the day.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And then, when you were finally ushered in front of the functionary who had the supreme power of putting that stamp of extension, he would make it nasty.",
      "word_count": 28
    }
  ],
